{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":924,"text":"Carlos,"},{"time":2477,"text":"the Vietnam vet Marine"},{"time":4054,"text":"who volunteered for three tours\nand got shot up in every one."},{"time":8650,"text":"In 1971, he was medically retired"},{"time":10776,"text":"because he had so much\nshrapnel in his body"},{"time":13099,"text":"that he was setting off metal detectors."},{"time":16279,"text":"For the next 42 years,\nhe suffered from nightmares,"},{"time":19404,"text":"extreme anxiety in public,"},{"time":21642,"text":"isolation, depression."},{"time":23677,"text":"He self-medicated with alcohol."},{"time":25605,"text":"He was married and divorced three times."},{"time":28535,"text":"Carlos had post-traumatic stress disorder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32129,"text":"Now, I became a psychologist\nto help mitigate human suffering,"},{"time":35730,"text":"and for the past 10 years, my target\nhas been the suffering caused by PTSD,"},{"time":40241,"text":"as experienced by veterans like Carlos."},{"time":43356,"text":"Until recently, the science of PTSD\njust wasn't there."},{"time":49161,"text":"And so, we didn't know what to do."},{"time":51561,"text":"We put some veterans on heavy drugs."},{"time":53949,"text":"Others we hospitalized\nand gave generic group therapy,"},{"time":56777,"text":"and others still we simply said to them,"},{"time":58899,"text":"\"Just go home and try to forget\nabout your experiences.\""},{"time":63534,"text":"More recently, we've tried therapy dogs,\nwilderness retreats --"},{"time":66901,"text":"many things which may\ntemporarily relieve stress,"},{"time":69846,"text":"but which don't actually eliminate\nPTSD symptoms over the long term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74654,"text":"But things have changed."},{"time":76451,"text":"And I am here to tell you\nthat we can now eliminate PTSD,"},{"time":81631,"text":"not just manage the symptoms,"},{"time":83482,"text":"and in huge numbers of veterans."},{"time":85054,"text":"Because new scientific research\nhas been able to show,"},{"time":88056,"text":"objectively, repeatedly,"},{"time":90458,"text":"which treatments actually\nget rid of symptoms and which do not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93957,"text":"Now as it turns out,"},{"time":95629,"text":"the best treatments for PTSD use\nmany of the very same training principles"},{"time":100883,"text":"that the military uses\nin preparing its trainees for war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106227,"text":"Now, making war --"},{"time":108254,"text":"this is something that we are good at."},{"time":110993,"text":"We humans have been making war\nsince before we were even fully human."},{"time":116006,"text":"And since then, we have gone\nfrom using stone and sinew"},{"time":119494,"text":"to developing the most sophisticated\nand devastating weapon systems imaginable."},{"time":124108,"text":"And to enable our warriors\nto use these weapons,"},{"time":126467,"text":"we employ the most cutting-edge\ntraining methods."},{"time":128812,"text":"We are good at making war."},{"time":130898,"text":"And we are good at training\nour warriors to fight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134687,"text":"Yet, when we consider the experience\nof the modern-day combat veteran,"},{"time":138200,"text":"we begin to see that we\nhave not been as good"},{"time":141411,"text":"at preparing them to come home."},{"time":143447,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":145731,"text":"Well, our ancestors lived\nimmersed in conflict,"},{"time":149029,"text":"and they fought right where they lived."},{"time":152094,"text":"So until only very recently\nin our evolutionary history,"},{"time":155132,"text":"there was hardly a need to learn\nhow to come home from war,"},{"time":158048,"text":"because we never really did."},{"time":161377,"text":"But thankfully, today,"},{"time":162643,"text":"most of humanity lives\nin far more peaceful societies,"},{"time":165682,"text":"and when there is conflict,\nwe, especially in the United States,"},{"time":169685,"text":"now have the technology to put\nour warriors through advanced training,"},{"time":173206,"text":"drop them in to fight\nanywhere on the globe"},{"time":176047,"text":"and when they're done,"},{"time":177530,"text":"jet them back to peacetime suburbia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180514,"text":"But just imagine for a moment\nwhat this must feel like."},{"time":185064,"text":"I've spoken with veterans who've told me"},{"time":187108,"text":"that one day they're in a brutal\nfirefight in Afghanistan"},{"time":190224,"text":"where they saw carnage and death,"},{"time":193867,"text":"and just three days later,\nthey found themselves"},{"time":196361,"text":"toting an ice chest\nto their kid's soccer game."},{"time":200405,"text":"\"Mindfuck\" is the most common term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203194,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204632,"text":"It's the most common term\nI've heard to describe that experience."},{"time":207775,"text":"And that's exactly what that is."},{"time":209323,"text":"Because while our warriors\nspend countless hours training for war,"},{"time":213336,"text":"we've only recently come to understand"},{"time":215253,"text":"that many require training\non how to return to civilian life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219642,"text":"Now, like any training, the best\nPTSD treatments require repetition."},{"time":223757,"text":"In the military,"},{"time":224932,"text":"we don't simply hand trainees\nMark-19 automatic grenade launchers"},{"time":228196,"text":"and say, \"Here's the trigger,\nhere's some ammo and good luck.\""},{"time":231412,"text":"No. We train them, on the range\nand in specific contexts,"},{"time":236132,"text":"over and over and over"},{"time":237842,"text":"until lifting their weapon\nand engaging their target"},{"time":240655,"text":"is so engrained into muscle memory"},{"time":242515,"text":"that it can be performed\nwithout even thinking,"},{"time":244867,"text":"even under the most stressful\nconditions you can imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248630,"text":"Now, the same holds\nfor training-based treatments."},{"time":251875,"text":"The first of these treatments\nis cognitive therapy,"},{"time":255230,"text":"and this is a kind\nof mental recalibration."},{"time":259166,"text":"When veterans come home from war,"},{"time":260819,"text":"their way of mentally framing\nthe world is calibrated"},{"time":263439,"text":"to an immensely\nmore dangerous environment."},{"time":266860,"text":"So when you try to overlay that mind frame\nonto a peacetime environment,"},{"time":272040,"text":"you get problems."},{"time":273269,"text":"You begin drowning in worries\nabout dangers that aren't present."},{"time":277748,"text":"You begin not trusting family or friends."},{"time":281935,"text":"Which is not to say there are no\ndangers in civilian life; there are."},{"time":286402,"text":"It's just that the probability\nof encountering them"},{"time":289118,"text":"compared to combat"},{"time":290412,"text":"is astronomically lower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293675,"text":"So we never advise veterans\nto turn off caution completely."},{"time":296839,"text":"We do train them, however,\nto adjust caution"},{"time":299247,"text":"according to where they are."},{"time":301685,"text":"If you find yourself\nin a bad neighborhood,"},{"time":304194,"text":"you turn it up."},{"time":305878,"text":"Out to dinner with family?"},{"time":307551,"text":"You turn it way down."},{"time":309975,"text":"We train veterans to be fiercely rational,"},{"time":313271,"text":"to systematically gauge\nthe actual statistical probability"},{"time":316849,"text":"of encountering, say, an IED\nhere in peacetime America."},{"time":321460,"text":"With enough practice,\nthose recalibrations stick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327193,"text":"The next of these treatments\nis exposure therapy,"},{"time":329531,"text":"and this is a kind of field training,"},{"time":332453,"text":"and the fastest of the proven\neffective treatments out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335974,"text":"You remember Carlos?"},{"time":337555,"text":"This was the treatment that he chose."},{"time":339869,"text":"And so we started off\nby giving him exercises,"},{"time":342333,"text":"for him, challenging ones:"},{"time":343663,"text":"going to a grocery store,"},{"time":345633,"text":"going to a shopping mall,\ngoing to a restaurant,"},{"time":348282,"text":"sitting with his back to the door."},{"time":351214,"text":"And, critically --"},{"time":353032,"text":"staying in these environments."},{"time":355791,"text":"Now, at first he was very anxious."},{"time":357525,"text":"He wanted to sit\nwhere he could scan the room,"},{"time":360041,"text":"where he could plan escape routes,"},{"time":361990,"text":"where he could get his hands\non a makeshift weapon."},{"time":365041,"text":"And he wanted to leave, but he didn't."},{"time":368390,"text":"He remembered his training\nin the Marine Corps,"},{"time":371285,"text":"and he pushed through his discomfort."},{"time":373530,"text":"And every time he did this,\nhis anxiety ratcheted down a little bit,"},{"time":376746,"text":"and then a little bit more\nand then a little bit more,"},{"time":379529,"text":"until in the end,"},{"time":380867,"text":"he had effectively relearned\nhow to sit in a public space"},{"time":386785,"text":"and just enjoy himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389704,"text":"He also listened to recordings\nof his combat experiences,"},{"time":393046,"text":"over and over and over."},{"time":395706,"text":"He listened until those memories\nno longer generated any anxiety."},{"time":400419,"text":"He processed his memories so much"},{"time":403005,"text":"that his brain no longer needed\nto return to those experiences"},{"time":406258,"text":"in his sleep."},{"time":408400,"text":"And when I spoke with him\na year after treatment had finished,"},{"time":411977,"text":"he told me,"},{"time":413372,"text":"\"Doc, this is the first time in 43 years"},{"time":418472,"text":"that I haven't had nightmares.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":421412,"text":"Now, this is different\nthan erasing a memory."},{"time":426087,"text":"Veterans will always remember\ntheir traumatic experiences,"},{"time":429106,"text":"but with enough practice,"},{"time":430787,"text":"those memories are no longer as raw\nor as painful as they once were."},{"time":436379,"text":"They don't feel emotionally\nlike they just happened yesterday,"},{"time":439964,"text":"and that is an immensely\nbetter place to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445985,"text":"But it's often difficult."},{"time":447677,"text":"And, like any training,\nit may not work for everybody."},{"time":452117,"text":"And there are trust issues."},{"time":453931,"text":"Sometimes I'm asked,"},{"time":455237,"text":"\"If you haven't been there, Doc,\nhow can you help me?\""},{"time":457915,"text":"Which is understandable."},{"time":460244,"text":"But at the point of returning\nto civilian life,"},{"time":464639,"text":"you do not require\nsomebody who's been there."},{"time":467985,"text":"You don't require training\nfor operations on the battlefield;"},{"time":471125,"text":"you require training on how to come home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478626,"text":"For the past 10 years of my work,"},{"time":481336,"text":"I have been exposed to detailed accounts"},{"time":484108,"text":"of the worst experiences\nthat you can imagine,"},{"time":486732,"text":"daily."},{"time":487985,"text":"And it hasn't always been easy."},{"time":490107,"text":"There have been times\nwhere I have just felt my heart break"},{"time":493496,"text":"or that I've absorbed too much."},{"time":496150,"text":"But these training-based\ntreatments work so well,"},{"time":499497,"text":"that whatever this work takes out of me,\nit puts back even more,"},{"time":502603,"text":"because I see people get better."},{"time":506754,"text":"I see people's lives transform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510656,"text":"Carlos can now enjoy outings\nwith his grandchildren,"},{"time":514018,"text":"which is something he couldn't even do\nwith his own children."},{"time":517638,"text":"And what's amazing to me\nis that after 43 years of suffering,"},{"time":521648,"text":"it only took him 10 weeks\nof intense training to get his life back."},{"time":526001,"text":"And when I spoke with him, he told me,"},{"time":528333,"text":"\"I know that I can't get those years back."},{"time":533088,"text":"But at least now, whatever days\nthat I have left on this Earth,"},{"time":538021,"text":"I can live them in peace.\""},{"time":541114,"text":"He also said, \"I hope that these\nyounger veterans don't wait"},{"time":544610,"text":"to get the help they need.\""},{"time":546588,"text":"And that's my hope, too."},{"time":549020,"text":"Because ..."},{"time":551003,"text":"this life is short,"},{"time":553383,"text":"and if you are fortunate enough\nto have survived war"},{"time":556579,"text":"or any kind of traumatic experience,"},{"time":558683,"text":"you owe it to yourself\nto live your life well."},{"time":562629,"text":"And you shouldn't wait\nto get the training you need"},{"time":565294,"text":"to make that happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568663,"text":"Now, the best way of ending\nhuman suffering caused by war"},{"time":574883,"text":"is to never go to war."},{"time":577422,"text":"But we are just not there\nyet as a species."},{"time":580157,"text":"Until we are,"},{"time":581441,"text":"the mental suffering that we create\nin our sons and in our daughters"},{"time":586698,"text":"when we send them off to fight"},{"time":588682,"text":"can be alleviated."},{"time":591675,"text":"But we must ensure that the science,\nthe energy level, the value"},{"time":597785,"text":"that we place on sending them off to war"},{"time":601516,"text":"is at the very least mirrored"},{"time":603450,"text":"in how well we prepare them\nto come back home to us."},{"time":607868,"text":"This much, we owe them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610186,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611393,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}